## Learning Objectives

By the end of this module, you will be able to:

* Understand how physical measurements are encoded as digital data
* Explain how digital images are composed of pixels and color values
* Convert between different number bases (binary, decimal, hexadecimal)
* Recognize representation as a key step in computational problem-solving
* Understand how parity bits detect errors in data transmission
* Explore classical and modern encryption techniques
